Interface Block

  • All Superinterfaces:
    HierarchicalScope<Declaration>, Scope<Declaration>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BlockImpl

    public interface Block
extends HierarchicalScope<Declaration>
    A block contains declarations. It is thus a Scope even if a separate SymbolTable is used in the attributed semantics in order to manage declarations.
